  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators have planned this project to evaluate the follow-up program after surgery
      due to cervical cancer and to explore the possibilities for different tests of Human
      Papilloma Virus (HPV) in contributing to the customization of the follow-up program.

      Purpose:

      The investigators effort is to provide the background for an evidence-based update of the
      follow-up program after surgery due to cervical cancer with the purpose of early diagnosis of
      recurrence affecting quality of life for as few women as possible.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
